Capesize Vessels at Anchor Decrease by 20%, Global Ports Says

-- B y   A l i s t a i r   H o l l o w a y
-- 
2011-03-14T09:00:28Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-14/capesize-vessels-at-anchor-decrease-by-20-global-ports-says.html
The number of capesize ships
waiting to load or unload cargo globally decreased 20 percent in
the week to March 11, according to a company that tracks port
delays.  There were 113 of the vessels anchored, down from 142 a
week earlier, Truro, England-based  Global Ports  said in an e-
mailed report sent yesterday.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alistair Holloway in  London  at 
 aholloway1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Claudia Carpenter at 
 ccarpenter2@bloomberg.net . 